is that has led to a
situation where we have

00:07:29.540 --> 00:07:31.581 align:middle line:84%
the sickest culture in
the history of the planet,

00:07:31.581 --> 00:07:33.710 align:middle line:84%
literally, the most obese
culture, the most cancer

00:07:33.710 --> 00:07:35.240 align:middle line:84%
ridden, the most
diabetic culture.

00:07:35.240 --> 00:07:36.379 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And out of touch.

00:07:36.379 --> 00:07:37.670 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: That's another factor.

00:07:37.670 --> 00:07:38.870 align:middle line:84%
Because it takes
you out of touch.

00:07:38.870 --> 00:07:40.560 align:middle line:84%
To medicalize takes
you out of touch.

00:07:40.560 --> 00:07:41.421 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, it does.

00:07:41.421 --> 00:07:42.920 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Medicine
is the middle man.

00:07:42.920 --> 00:07:44.660 align:middle line:84%
The word "med"
comes from "middle."

00:07:44.660 --> 00:07:45.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:07:45.050 --> 00:07:46.280 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: It's a
middle man between,

00:07:46.280 --> 00:07:48.655 align:middle line:84%
it's like, in the old days,
the priest was the middle man

00:07:48.655 --> 00:07:49.730 align:middle line:90%
between God and you.

00:07:49.730 --> 00:07:51.950 align:middle line:84%
Now, the medical
man is the interface

00:07:51.950 --> 00:07:53.110 align:middle line:90%
between you and your body.

00:07:53.110 --> 00:07:54.620 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, it's kind
of a broken system.

00:07:54.620 --> 00:07:55.512 align:middle line:90%
You go to a doctor.

00:07:55.512 --> 00:07:57.470 align:middle line:84%
And they have 15 minutes
to tell you everything

00:07:57.470 --> 00:07:58.970 align:middle line:90%
that they possibly can.

00:07:58.970 --> 00:07:59.220 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: It's a broken system.

00:07:59.220 --> 00:08:00.590 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you just
listen and then you

00:08:00.590 --> 00:08:02.180 align:middle line:84%
have to listen and hear
everything they say.

00:08:02.180 --> 00:08:02.310 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: All that.

00:08:02.310 --> 00:08:02.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Take it all in.

00:08:02.720 --> 00:08:04.820 align:middle line:84%
And then you just say,
OK, I'll do what you said.

00:08:04.820 --> 00:08:07.237 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: I should tell you,
there's two kinds of diseases.

00:08:07.237 --> 00:08:08.861 align:middle line:84%
There's two kinds of
bodily breakdowns,

00:08:08.861 --> 00:08:10.940 align:middle line:84%
two kinds of traumas
that the body can suffer.

00:08:10.940 --> 00:08:13.106 align:middle line:84%
There's chronic trauma,
long term trauma and there's

00:08:13.106 --> 00:08:15.780 align:middle line:84%
short term, accidents
and things falling--

00:08:15.780 --> 00:08:16.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Acute.

00:08:16.580 --> 00:08:16.880 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: --on your head.

00:08:16.880 --> 00:08:17.870 align:middle line:90%
Acute, right.

00:08:17.870 --> 00:08:20.630 align:middle line:84%
So in pharmacy, we say
there's two kinds of medicine.

00:08:20.630 --> 00:08:22.430 align:middle line:84%
We say there's heroic
medicine and there's

00:08:22.430 --> 00:08:24.140 align:middle line:90%
ambulatory medicine.

00:08:24.140 --> 00:08:26.650 align:middle line:84%
Heroic medicine is the medicine
of the hero, save your life.

00:08:26.650 --> 00:08:28.072 align:middle line:84%
You get hit in the
head, you break

00:08:28.072 --> 00:08:29.780 align:middle line:84%
your leg, something
you need stitched up,

00:08:29.780 --> 00:08:30.920 align:middle line:90%
praise God for the surgeons.

00:08:30.920 --> 00:08:31.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Great.

00:08:31.720 --> 00:08:34.429 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: OK, praise God for
that kind of modern medicine.

00:08:34.429 --> 00:08:35.990 align:middle line:84%
But there's a second
kind of disease

00:08:35.990 --> 00:08:38.900 align:middle line:84%
that has really only hit us over
the last 5,000 to 10,000 years.

00:08:38.900 --> 00:08:40.520 align:middle line:84%
And we didn't really
grow up with it.

00:08:40.520 --> 00:08:42.359 align:middle line:84%
And that's chronic
degenerative disease.

00:08:42.359 --> 00:08:43.159 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:08:43.159 --> 00:08:46.220 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: If modern medicine gets
an A-plus for treating broken

00:08:46.220 --> 00:08:48.170 align:middle line:84%
bones, which it does,
and repairing things--

00:08:48.170 --> 00:08:48.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Triage.

00:08:48.560 --> 00:08:50.226 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: --and stitching
things back on.

00:08:50.226 --> 00:08:53.030 align:middle line:84%
And if it gets an A-plus
here, it gets an F-minus here.

00:08:53.030 --> 00:08:55.750 align:middle line:84%
Modern medicine is riding on
the coattails of penicillin,

00:08:55.750 --> 00:08:56.970 align:middle line:90%
is what I like to say.

00:08:56.970 --> 00:08:59.740 align:middle line:84%
As penicillin came around,
and if you can remember,

00:08:59.740 --> 00:09:03.291 align:middle line:84%
if you can imagine how
life was before penicillin,

00:09:03.291 --> 00:09:05.040 align:middle line:84%
you know, you catch a
cold, you were dead.

00:09:05.040 --> 00:09:06.290 align:middle line:90%
You could potentially die.

00:09:06.290 --> 00:09:07.750 align:middle line:84%
You know, babies
died all the time.

00:09:07.750 --> 00:09:09.979 align:middle line:84%
People would have six
babies, six children and five

00:09:09.979 --> 00:09:11.270 align:middle line:90%
of them would die before they--

00:09:11.270 --> 00:09:11.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:09:11.510 --> 00:09:13.160 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Can imagine
the world that way?

00:09:13.160 --> 00:09:14.660 align:middle line:84%
And you never knew when
it was gonna happen.

00:09:14.660 --> 00:09:15.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Uh-huh.

00:09:15.030 --> 00:09:17.030 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Can you imagine
living this way, right?

00:09:17.030 --> 00:09:20.630 align:middle line:84%
So then, penicillin came
along, and it was all over.

00:09:20.630 --> 00:09:23.709 align:middle line:84%
So people got the
idea that medicine--

00:09:23.709 --> 00:09:24.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Fixes everything.

00:09:24.750 --> 00:09:26.247 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Everything.

00:09:26.247 --> 00:09:28.580 align:middle line:84%
And so what happened was
because the drug companies were

00:09:28.580 --> 00:09:30.451 align:middle line:84%
entrenched and there
was a lot of money

00:09:30.451 --> 00:09:32.700 align:middle line:84%
to be made in medicine-- the
profit margin on medicine

00:09:32.700 --> 00:09:34.280 align:middle line:90%
is ungodly.

00:09:34.280 --> 00:09:35.120 align:middle line:90%
It's ridiculous.

00:09:35.120 --> 00:09:36.770 align:middle line:84%
You can't even imagine
what the profit margin is.

00:09:36.770 --> 00:09:38.300 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We hear
about it in the news.

00:09:38.300 --> 00:09:39.341 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: It's ridiculous.

00:09:39.341 --> 00:09:40.354 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ridiculous.

00:09:40.354 --> 00:09:42.020 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: So the
pharmaceutical companies

00:09:42.020 --> 00:09:43.430 align:middle line:84%
start to try to
discover more and more.

00:09:43.430 --> 00:09:44.959 align:middle line:84%
And then they had
to create markets.

00:09:44.959 --> 00:09:46.250 align:middle line:90%
So they had to create diseases.

00:09:46.250 --> 00:09:48.184 align:middle line:84%
And they weren't
interested necessarily

00:09:48.184 --> 00:09:50.600 align:middle line:84%
in helping people with things
that would really help them,

00:09:50.600 --> 00:09:55.040 align:middle line:84%
with causes, but rather
keeping them riding along

00:09:55.040 --> 00:09:56.440 align:middle line:90%
the pharmaceutical gravy train.

00:09:56.440 --> 00:09:58.190 align:middle line:84%
So they got their
statin drug every month.

00:09:58.190 --> 00:09:59.720 align:middle line:84%
They get their diabetes
drug every month,

00:09:59.720 --> 00:10:00.560 align:middle line:90%
you get your thyroid--

00:10:00.560 --> 00:10:01.790 align:middle line:84%
You know, the worst
thing I ever hear,

00:10:01.790 --> 00:10:03.456 align:middle line:84%
one of the most
horrifying things I hear

00:10:03.456 --> 00:10:05.137 align:middle line:84%
is when people
say, my doctor told

00:10:05.137 --> 00:10:07.220 align:middle line:84%
I'm gonna be on that drug
for the rest of my life.

00:10:07.220 --> 00:10:07.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:10:07.860 --> 00:10:10.151 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: And I always tell
people, if you're on a drug,

00:10:10.151 --> 00:10:12.200 align:middle line:84%
your number-one health
goal is to figure out

00:10:12.200 --> 00:10:13.566 align:middle line:90%
how to get off that drug.

00:10:13.566 --> 00:10:15.440 align:middle line:84%
Because I'm telling you
this as a pharmacist,

00:10:15.440 --> 00:10:17.600 align:middle line:84%
there isn't a single
prescription drug

00:10:17.600 --> 00:10:21.530 align:middle line:84%
that can not only not fix your
chronic degenerative disease,

00:10:21.530 --> 00:10:25.160 align:middle line:84%
but that is not going to
cause, in the long term,

00:10:25.160 --> 00:10:28.191 align:middle line:84%
a toxicity and/or a
nutritional deficiency.

00:10:28.191 --> 00:10:29.690 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There isn't
one single drug.

00:10:29.690 --> 00:10:31.010 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Not one single drug.

00:10:31.010 --> 00:10:32.645 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So no matter
them saying it's benign,

00:10:32.645 --> 00:10:33.650 align:middle line:84%
that this doesn't have
any side effects--

00:10:33.650 --> 00:10:34.895 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: No benign, no benign.

00:10:34.895 --> 00:10:35.150 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: There's no such thing.

00:10:35.150 --> 00:10:37.270 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Because when
your body takes a drug,

00:10:37.270 --> 00:10:38.900 align:middle line:84%
the number-one side
effect of drugs

00:10:38.900 --> 00:10:40.890 align:middle line:84%
is nausea and
vomiting and diarrhea.

00:10:40.890 --> 00:10:41.690 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:10:41.690 --> 00:10:45.310 align:middle line:84%
Because when you take a drug,
your body wants that out of you

00:10:45.310 --> 00:10:46.250 align:middle line:90%
quickly.

00:10:46.250 --> 00:10:48.140 align:middle line:84%
And when they dose
you with a drug,

00:10:48.140 --> 00:10:51.350 align:middle line:84%
they have to dose you at a
dose that is 10 times higher

00:10:51.350 --> 00:10:54.110 align:middle line:84%
than the dose your body is
using because your liver will

00:10:54.110 --> 00:10:56.110 align:middle line:90%
immediately clear that drug out.

00:10:56.110 --> 00:10:56.910 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:10:56.910 --> 00:10:58.400 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: So they have to
give you an extra high dose

00:10:58.400 --> 00:11:00.590 align:middle line:84%
because your body is
like, I don't want you.

00:11:00.590 --> 00:11:01.880 align:middle line:90%
I want you out of here.

00:11:01.880 --> 00:11:03.330 align:middle line:90%
This is the nature of drugs.

00:11:03.330 --> 00:11:05.871 align:middle line:84%
So when you take a prescription
drug, the most gentle, benign

00:11:05.871 --> 00:11:08.930 align:middle line:84%
whatever, no side effects,
what you're not being told

00:11:08.930 --> 00:11:11.480 align:middle line:84%
is your vitamin C has
to go to your liver

00:11:11.480 --> 00:11:14.930 align:middle line:84%
to detoxify that drug so
it's not in your heart.

00:11:14.930 --> 00:11:17.184 align:middle line:84%
Your B complex has to be
used to detoxify the drug,

00:11:17.184 --> 00:11:18.350 align:middle line:90%
your magnesium, your copper.

00:11:18.350 --> 00:11:21.860 align:middle line:84%
You run higher risks of
nutritional deficiency states

00:11:21.860 --> 00:11:24.770 align:middle line:84%
after you take your drug
because your body is allocating

00:11:24.770 --> 00:11:28.310 align:middle line:84%
its precious resources to
the detoxification machinery

00:11:28.310 --> 00:11:30.200 align:middle line:84%
to get that stuff
out of your system.

00:11:30.200 --> 00:11:32.157 align:middle line:84%
And that doesn't show
up on the side effects.

00:11:32.157 --> 00:11:33.740 align:middle line:84%
That doesn't show
up as a side effect.

00:11:33.740 --> 00:11:36.950 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Interesting, so if
we were to learn that most

00:11:36.950 --> 00:11:39.200 align:middle line:84%
of our healing had to
do with our emotional

00:11:39.200 --> 00:11:40.500 align:middle line:90%
and our physical--

00:11:40.500 --> 00:11:41.390 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: SMEP.

00:11:41.390 --> 00:11:42.560 align:middle line:90%
I call it SMEP.

00:11:42.560 --> 00:11:46.190 align:middle line:84%
Spiritual, mental,
emotional, physical.

00:11:46.190 --> 00:11:48.090 align:middle line:84%
Health has all
dimensions in place.

00:11:48.090 --> 00:11:50.150 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There's
no profit in that.

00:11:50.150 --> 00:11:53.390 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: You can-- Look, right
now, your body is breaking down

00:11:53.390 --> 00:11:54.710 align:middle line:90%
as you're talking to me.

00:11:54.710 --> 00:11:56.630 align:middle line:90%
But it's also building up.

00:11:56.630 --> 00:11:59.600 align:middle line:84%
At any given moment, your body
is in this balance of breakdown

00:11:59.600 --> 00:12:00.400 align:middle line:90%
and build up.

00:12:00.400 --> 00:12:02.985 align:middle line:84%
And what we say in chemistry,
we say anabolism and catabolism.

00:12:02.985 --> 00:12:04.870 align:middle line:84%
You may have heard
of anabolic steroids.

00:12:04.870 --> 00:12:05.850 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hm.

00:12:05.850 --> 00:12:08.030 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: So "anabolism"
means "building."

00:12:08.030 --> 00:12:09.920 align:middle line:84%
"Catabolism" means
"breaking down."

00:12:09.920 --> 00:12:13.040 align:middle line:84%
At any given moment, you
are in this dynamic dance

00:12:13.040 --> 00:12:14.390 align:middle line:90%
of anabolism and catabolism.

00:12:14.390 --> 00:12:16.390 align:middle line:84%
And when you're young and
beautiful and healthy,

00:12:16.390 --> 00:12:19.400 align:middle line:84%
you're way anabolic,
net anabolic.

00:12:19.400 --> 00:12:20.450 align:middle line:90%
You're net building.

00:12:20.450 --> 00:12:21.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Growing, growing.

00:12:21.560 --> 00:12:22.220 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: You're building.

00:12:22.220 --> 00:12:24.650 align:middle line:84%
You're still breaking down,
but you're net anabolic.

00:12:24.650 --> 00:12:27.590 align:middle line:90%
As we age, that reverses.

00:12:27.590 --> 00:12:29.450 align:middle line:84%
So the point is is
that we have access

00:12:29.450 --> 00:12:32.150 align:middle line:84%
to these anabolic systems
because we're constantly

00:12:32.150 --> 00:12:33.260 align:middle line:90%
building anyway.

00:12:33.260 --> 00:12:36.350 align:middle line:84%
So what we want to do is we
want to amplify and enhance

00:12:36.350 --> 00:12:37.310 align:middle line:90%
the anabolism.

00:12:37.310 --> 00:12:38.330 align:middle line:90%
That's what disease is.

00:12:38.330 --> 00:12:40.130 align:middle line:84%
Disease is when
you're net catabolic.

00:12:40.130 --> 00:12:40.880 align:middle line:90%
You're net breaking down.

00:12:40.880 --> 00:12:42.040 align:middle line:84%
So what we want do is
we want to figure out

00:12:42.040 --> 00:12:43.730 align:middle line:90%
how to reverse that equation.

00:12:43.730 --> 00:12:45.200 align:middle line:90%
The body can turn on a dime.

00:12:45.200 --> 00:12:45.620 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:12:45.620 --> 00:12:46.400 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: But we need
to turn on a dime.

00:12:46.400 --> 00:12:48.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: No matter
what age, it can?

00:12:48.220 --> 00:12:48.480 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Depending.

00:12:48.480 --> 00:12:48.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:12:48.740 --> 00:12:50.090 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: I believe,
theoretically,

00:12:50.090 --> 00:12:50.750 align:middle line:90%
I don't see why it shouldn't.

00:12:50.750 --> 00:12:51.410 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You could slow it down.

00:12:51.410 --> 00:12:53.701 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: We should be able
slow it down, theoretically.

00:12:53.701 --> 00:12:55.944 align:middle line:84%
Theoretically, I mean,
if you believe that idea,

00:12:55.944 --> 00:12:57.110 align:middle line:90%
you should be able to do it.

00:12:57.110 --> 00:12:59.570 align:middle line:84%
Now, we live in
a polluted world.

00:12:59.570 --> 00:13:01.880 align:middle line:90%
We live in a world that's got--

00:13:01.880 --> 00:13:03.240 align:middle line:90%
we have to drink polluted water.

00:13:03.240 --> 00:13:04.406 align:middle line:90%
We got to eat polluted food.

00:13:04.406 --> 00:13:06.397 align:middle line:84%
We got to breathe polluted
air, not to mention

00:13:06.397 --> 00:13:08.480 align:middle line:84%
all the spiritual assaults
and the mental assaults

00:13:08.480 --> 00:13:09.604 align:middle line:90%
and the emotional assaults.

00:13:09.604 --> 00:13:12.530 align:middle line:84%
So we're never going to be able
to test that theory that we

00:13:12.530 --> 00:13:13.670 align:middle line:90%
can live forever.

00:13:13.670 --> 00:13:16.070 align:middle line:84%
But we can certainly age
much more gracefully.

00:13:16.070 --> 00:13:18.620 align:middle line:84%
We don't have to break down as
fast as we're breaking down.

00:13:18.620 --> 00:13:20.990 align:middle line:84%
Do you know this is the
third year in a row where

00:13:20.990 --> 00:13:22.220 align:middle line:90%
life expectancy is dropping?

00:13:22.220 --> 00:13:23.730 align:middle line:90%
OK, I just read it today.

00:13:23.730 --> 00:13:24.530 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:13:24.530 --> 00:13:28.509 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Third year in a row
where life expectancy-- where

00:13:28.509 --> 00:13:30.050 align:middle line:84%
the further generations
are not going

00:13:30.050 --> 00:13:31.310 align:middle line:84%
live-- this is the first
time this has ever happened,

00:13:31.310 --> 00:13:32.290 align:middle line:90%
the last couple of years.

00:13:32.290 --> 00:13:33.331 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That makes sense.

00:13:33.331 --> 00:13:36.002 align:middle line:84%
What is the story behind the
Gordian knot, the loop and--

00:13:36.002 --> 00:13:38.210 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Well, I'll give
you the abbreviated version.

00:13:38.210 --> 00:13:39.720 align:middle line:84%
Because I don't really know
the whole detailed version.

00:13:39.720 --> 00:13:41.422 align:middle line:84%
But I'll tell you
the point of it.

00:13:41.422 --> 00:13:44.000 align:middle line:84%
So Alexander the Great
was doing his little thing

00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:47.820 align:middle line:84%
in 400 BC or 300 BC,
whenever he was doing it.

00:13:47.820 --> 00:13:49.300 align:middle line:90%
And he came to this country.

00:13:49.300 --> 00:13:52.399 align:middle line:84%
And he found an ox cart
that was tied to a tree.

00:13:52.399 --> 00:13:54.440 align:middle line:84%
And he said, what is this
ox cart tied to a tree?

00:13:54.440 --> 00:13:57.500 align:middle line:84%
And he says, well,
somebody left this ox

00:13:57.500 --> 00:13:59.960 align:middle line:84%
cart tied to this tree
with this heavy duty knot.

00:13:59.960 --> 00:14:03.580 align:middle line:84%
And the legend is, whoever
can untie this knot, whoever

00:14:03.580 --> 00:14:05.660 align:middle line:84%
can get this ox
cart off this tree

00:14:05.660 --> 00:14:07.520 align:middle line:84%
is going to become
King of Gordia.

00:14:07.520 --> 00:14:10.605 align:middle line:84%
And people had been coming for
decades maybe even centuries

00:14:10.605 --> 00:14:12.230 align:middle line:84%
to try to untie this
knot so they could

00:14:12.230 --> 00:14:14.720 align:middle line:84%
become King of Gordia
and to untie the knot

00:14:14.720 --> 00:14:15.610 align:middle line:90%
and get the cart out.

00:14:15.610 --> 00:14:16.503 align:middle line:84%
And they couldn't
do it because it

00:14:16.503 --> 00:14:17.890 align:middle line:90%
was an incredibly complex knot.

00:14:17.890 --> 00:14:19.842 align:middle line:84%
And so Alexander the
Great, being Alexander

00:14:19.842 --> 00:14:22.300 align:middle line:84%
the Great trained by Socrates
and being great and all that,

00:14:22.300 --> 00:14:23.589 align:middle line:90%
right, he goes, oh, yeah?

00:14:23.589 --> 00:14:25.380 align:middle line:84%
Takes out his knife,
he goes [VOCALIZING]..

00:14:25.380 --> 00:14:26.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [LAUGHING]

00:14:26.180 --> 00:14:27.890 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: And he cuts
the knot, right?

00:14:27.890 --> 00:14:29.810 align:middle line:90%
I'm King of Gordia, right?

00:14:29.810 --> 00:14:31.710 align:middle line:84%
And that's the story
of the Gordian knot.

00:14:31.710 --> 00:14:35.630 align:middle line:84%
The point being is you don't
need to untie a bunch of knots.

00:14:35.630 --> 00:14:37.640 align:middle line:84%
You just need to
cut to the chase.

00:14:37.640 --> 00:14:39.260 align:middle line:84%
And when it comes
to health, we've

00:14:39.260 --> 00:14:42.410 align:middle line:84%
got all these diagnostics
and drugs and testing

00:14:42.410 --> 00:14:45.450 align:middle line:84%
and doctors and specialists
and all of this.

00:14:45.450 --> 00:14:49.250 align:middle line:84%
We know all the molecular
interactions that take place

00:14:49.250 --> 00:14:50.882 align:middle line:90%
at the sub-cellular level.

00:14:50.882 --> 00:14:52.590 align:middle line:84%
And I go to the library,
medical library.

00:14:52.590 --> 00:14:53.700 align:middle line:84%
I love going to the
medical library.

00:14:53.700 --> 00:14:55.250 align:middle line:84%
And they have books
and books and books

00:14:55.250 --> 00:14:56.875 align:middle line:84%
and everything you
could possibly know,

00:14:56.875 --> 00:14:59.570 align:middle line:84%
every enzyme reaction and every
interaction between chemicals.

00:14:59.570 --> 00:15:00.370 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Sure.

00:15:00.370 --> 00:15:01.790 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: We have
all this wisdom.

00:15:01.790 --> 00:15:06.200 align:middle line:84%
But we're so sick because we're
worried about how many angels

00:15:06.200 --> 00:15:08.140 align:middle line:84%
can dance on the head
of a pin when we just

00:15:08.140 --> 00:15:09.140 align:middle line:90%
got to cut to the chase.

00:15:09.140 --> 00:15:10.598 align:middle line:84%
The cut to the
chase in the body is

00:15:10.598 --> 00:15:14.090 align:middle line:84%
how does the body, from a
physical perspective, what

00:15:14.090 --> 00:15:19.700 align:middle line:84%
is the most fragile and
vulnerable junction in the body

00:15:19.700 --> 00:15:21.200 align:middle line:90%
from a physical perspective?

00:15:21.200 --> 00:15:23.590 align:middle line:84%
In other words, the
body lives in the outs--

00:15:23.590 --> 00:15:25.340 align:middle line:84%
This is us, and we
live in a world.

00:15:25.340 --> 00:15:26.140 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:15:26.140 --> 00:15:27.710 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: What is
the juncture, what

00:15:27.710 --> 00:15:29.870 align:middle line:84%
is the interaction
point between the world

00:15:29.870 --> 00:15:32.060 align:middle line:84%
and our body from
a physical level?

00:15:32.060 --> 00:15:32.980 align:middle line:90%
The gut.

00:15:32.980 --> 00:15:33.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:15:33.580 --> 00:15:35.240 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: This is the
core of everything.

00:15:35.240 --> 00:15:35.850 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, interesting.

00:15:35.850 --> 00:15:37.896 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: This is the
core of all diseases

00:15:37.896 --> 00:15:39.770 align:middle line:84%
because this is where
the outside world meets

00:15:39.770 --> 00:15:41.000 align:middle line:90%
the inside world.

00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:42.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: We internalize things.

00:15:42.250 --> 00:15:43.940 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: We internalize food.

00:15:43.940 --> 00:15:46.530 align:middle line:84%
Well, yes, because this is
the solar plexus center.

00:15:46.530 --> 00:15:50.260 align:middle line:84%
And there's a whole
spiritual idea here, as well.

00:15:50.260 --> 00:15:52.010 align:middle line:84%
And this is your major
nerve plexus, here,

00:15:52.010 --> 00:15:52.850 align:middle line:90%
next to your brain.

00:15:52.850 --> 00:15:53.000 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hm, mental.

00:15:53.000 --> 00:15:53.960 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: This is
the second brain.

00:15:53.960 --> 00:15:54.760 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hm.

00:15:54.760 --> 00:15:58.760 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: But from a purely
physical perspective,

00:15:58.760 --> 00:16:01.400 align:middle line:84%
what we put in our
body through our mouth

00:16:01.400 --> 00:16:06.620 align:middle line:84%
is the critical nexus between
health and lack thereof.

00:16:06.620 --> 00:16:08.312 align:middle line:84%
That's how you slice
the Gordian knot.

00:16:08.312 --> 00:16:09.770 align:middle line:84%
And I deal with
people all the time

00:16:09.770 --> 00:16:11.630 align:middle line:84%
who have got multiple
health challenges.

00:16:11.630 --> 00:16:12.680 align:middle line:84%
You should see
the letters I get.

00:16:12.680 --> 00:16:14.360 align:middle line:84%
And I get hundreds
of letters a month.

00:16:14.360 --> 00:16:17.300 align:middle line:84%
People have high blood pressure
and diabetes and thyroid

00:16:17.300 --> 00:16:19.937 align:middle line:84%
problems and blindness and
their hair is falling out

00:16:19.937 --> 00:16:20.770 align:middle line:90%
and they can't walk.

00:16:20.770 --> 00:16:21.680 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it's endless.

00:16:21.680 --> 00:16:23.240 align:middle line:84%
And some of these,
this is the same person

00:16:23.240 --> 00:16:23.990 align:middle line:90%
with all of these things.

00:16:23.990 --> 00:16:24.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hm.

00:16:24.480 --> 00:16:25.780 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: So what do you do?

00:16:25.780 --> 00:16:27.620 align:middle line:84%
If you go to the
medical model, you'll

00:16:27.620 --> 00:16:29.030 align:middle line:90%
go to an endocrinologist.

00:16:29.030 --> 00:16:29.825 align:middle line:90%
You'll go to a GI specialist.

00:16:29.825 --> 00:16:30.290 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:16:30.290 --> 00:16:32.180 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: You'll go
to an orthopedic guy.

00:16:32.180 --> 00:16:33.650 align:middle line:84%
You'll go to this
doctor and that doctor.

00:16:33.650 --> 00:16:34.980 align:middle line:84%
You have this test
and that test.

00:16:34.980 --> 00:16:36.145 align:middle line:84%
They'll give you
this drug and that--

00:16:36.145 --> 00:16:37.311 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Chasing the illness.

00:16:37.311 --> 00:16:40.340 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Cut to the chase,
slice the Gordian knot,

00:16:40.340 --> 00:16:42.630 align:middle line:84%
go right to your gut
from a physical level.

00:16:42.630 --> 00:16:43.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:16:43.430 --> 00:16:44.513 align:middle line:90%
All things stem from that?

00:16:44.513 --> 00:16:46.260 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Fast for three days.

00:16:46.260 --> 00:16:47.420 align:middle line:90%
Watch what happens.

00:16:47.420 --> 00:16:49.940 align:middle line:84%
At that's for all
disease, all diseases.

00:16:49.940 --> 00:16:52.160 align:middle line:84%
And I could tell you the
mech-- and it's fascinating.

00:16:52.160 --> 00:16:54.029 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to brush off
the mechanics behind it

00:16:54.029 --> 00:16:55.070 align:middle line:90%
or the science behind it.

00:16:55.070 --> 00:16:56.330 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No, I want to hear it.

00:16:56.330 --> 00:17:00.890 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: The gut is where
the major determining factor

00:17:00.890 --> 00:17:02.900 align:middle line:84%
between whether your
interpretation of the world

00:17:02.900 --> 00:17:04.880 align:middle line:90%
is safe or not safe resides.

00:17:04.880 --> 00:17:06.770 align:middle line:84%
You have a defensive
system in your body

00:17:06.770 --> 00:17:09.180 align:middle line:84%
that interprets everything
as safe or not safe.

00:17:09.180 --> 00:17:11.068 align:middle line:84%
What is that defensive
system called?

00:17:11.068 --> 00:17:12.359 align:middle line:90%
It's called your immune system.

00:17:12.359 --> 00:17:12.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, OK.

00:17:12.730 --> 00:17:13.190 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: OK?

00:17:13.190 --> 00:17:15.290 align:middle line:84%
So your immune system is
your defensive system.

00:17:15.290 --> 00:17:17.359 align:middle line:84%
It is the major system
in the body that

00:17:17.359 --> 00:17:18.859 align:middle line:84%
determines whether
the world is safe

00:17:18.859 --> 00:17:20.839 align:middle line:84%
or whether what you're
doing is safe or not safe.

00:17:20.839 --> 00:17:21.639 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:17:21.639 --> 00:17:23.660 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: The immune system
is housed in the gut.

00:17:23.660 --> 00:17:25.490 align:middle line:90%
It lives in the gut.

00:17:25.490 --> 00:17:27.470 align:middle line:84%
All disease, you probably
heard this term--

00:17:27.470 --> 00:17:29.870 align:middle line:84%
and I'm talking here now
chronic, degenerative disease,

00:17:29.870 --> 00:17:31.670 align:middle line:90%
diabetes, Alzheimer's disease--

00:17:31.670 --> 00:17:34.702 align:middle line:84%
all diseases have some
basis in an I-word

00:17:34.702 --> 00:17:37.160 align:middle line:84%
that everybody talks about but
nobody ever says what it is.

00:17:37.160 --> 00:17:38.390 align:middle line:90%
And that's inflammation.

00:17:38.390 --> 00:17:38.830 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:17:38.830 --> 00:17:39.170 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Right?

00:17:39.170 --> 00:17:39.530 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes?

00:17:39.530 --> 00:17:40.060 align:middle line:90%
For sure.

00:17:40.060 --> 00:17:41.510 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: But what
is inflammation?

00:17:41.510 --> 00:17:41.930 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:17:41.930 --> 00:17:42.960 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Your body's
reaction to something.

00:17:42.960 --> 00:17:44.330 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: But
specifically, what is it?

00:17:44.330 --> 00:17:45.204 align:middle line:90%
Yes, it's a reaction.

00:17:45.204 --> 00:17:46.395 align:middle line:90%
That's exactly what it is.

00:17:46.395 --> 00:17:47.270 align:middle line:90%
You go to the doctor.

00:17:47.270 --> 00:17:48.645 align:middle line:84%
If you go to
medical school, they

00:17:48.645 --> 00:17:50.540 align:middle line:90%
say dolor, calor, rubor, tumor.

00:17:50.540 --> 00:17:51.650 align:middle line:90%
"Dolor" means pain.

00:17:51.650 --> 00:17:52.840 align:middle line:90%
"Calor" means heat.

00:17:52.840 --> 00:17:53.930 align:middle line:90%
"Rubor" means redness.

00:17:53.930 --> 00:17:55.325 align:middle line:90%
"Tumor" means swelling.

00:17:55.325 --> 00:17:57.800 align:middle line:84%
OK, that's the four markers
that doctors will tell you.

00:17:57.800 --> 00:17:57.920 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:17:57.920 --> 00:17:59.670 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: You learn
that in medical school.

00:17:59.670 --> 00:18:04.040 align:middle line:84%
But inflammation can really be
simplified as a beaver's damn.

00:18:04.040 --> 00:18:05.760 align:middle line:84%
It's a way the body
protects itself.

00:18:05.760 --> 00:18:06.140 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:18:06.140 --> 00:18:07.014 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: It's a wall.

00:18:07.014 --> 00:18:08.617 align:middle line:90%
It's an airbag in your car.

00:18:08.617 --> 00:18:09.950 align:middle line:90%
And that's what inflammation is.

00:18:09.950 --> 00:18:12.590 align:middle line:84%
It's the calling card
or the manifestation

00:18:12.590 --> 00:18:13.960 align:middle line:90%
of the immune system.

00:18:13.960 --> 00:18:17.322 align:middle line:84%
All diseases have this
aspect of protection,

00:18:17.322 --> 00:18:20.630 align:middle line:84%
of defense and protection,
of the body protecting itself

00:18:20.630 --> 00:18:22.890 align:middle line:90%
from something.

00:18:22.890 --> 00:18:24.440 align:middle line:90%
It's a defensive response.

00:18:24.440 --> 00:18:26.510 align:middle line:84%
So a protective response
is a defensive response.

00:18:26.510 --> 00:18:28.750 align:middle line:84%
When you have-- this is
so important now, OK?

00:18:28.750 --> 00:18:29.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hm.

00:18:29.110 --> 00:18:29.870 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: This is
the Gordian knot.

00:18:29.870 --> 00:18:32.000 align:middle line:84%
We're slicing through
for all disease.

00:18:32.000 --> 00:18:34.100 align:middle line:84%
When you have a
defensive response,

00:18:34.100 --> 00:18:36.570 align:middle line:84%
if you want to eliminate
that defensive response,

00:18:36.570 --> 00:18:38.810 align:middle line:84%
what's the number-one
thing you have to know?

00:18:38.810 --> 00:18:40.160 align:middle line:90%
What is the offending agent?

00:18:40.160 --> 00:18:41.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Stop eating it up, yes.

00:18:41.030 --> 00:18:42.740 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: What is the offending
agent that's triggering

00:18:42.740 --> 00:18:43.850 align:middle line:90%
the defensive response?

00:18:43.850 --> 00:18:46.610 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you have a defensive
response in the body,

00:18:46.610 --> 00:18:49.840 align:middle line:84%
that means an offending agent
has gotten into the body.

00:18:49.840 --> 00:18:52.400 align:middle line:84%
So how do offending agents get
into-- this is all diseases

00:18:52.400 --> 00:18:53.460 align:middle line:90%
I'm talking about here--

00:18:53.460 --> 00:18:55.890 align:middle line:84%
how do offending agents
get into the body?

00:18:55.890 --> 00:18:57.140 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Well, you ingest them.

00:18:57.140 --> 00:18:58.230 align:middle line:90%
You breathe them.

00:18:58.230 --> 00:18:59.030 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:18:59.030 --> 00:19:00.946 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: You breathe
them to a certain extent.

00:19:00.946 --> 00:19:04.510 align:middle line:84%
You can inject them through
your skin to a certain extent.

00:19:04.510 --> 00:19:07.690 align:middle line:84%
But for the most part, what
do we do five times a day?

00:19:07.690 --> 00:19:08.490 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Eat.

00:19:08.490 --> 00:19:10.070 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Exactly.

00:19:10.070 --> 00:19:11.720 align:middle line:90%
What do we do way too much of?

00:19:11.720 --> 00:19:12.110 align:middle line:90%
Eat.

00:19:12.110 --> 00:19:12.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Eat.

00:19:12.500 --> 00:19:13.570 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: And what are we eating?

00:19:13.570 --> 00:19:14.900 align:middle line:84%
Do you think we're eating
the same kind of food

00:19:14.900 --> 00:19:17.200 align:middle line:84%
our bodies crave and need and
desire and have grown up with?

00:19:17.200 --> 00:19:18.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's whatever is
in front of us now, mm-hm.

00:19:18.770 --> 00:19:19.350 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: And whatever is--

00:19:19.350 --> 00:19:20.391 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's on the menu.

00:19:20.391 --> 00:19:23.150 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: 90% of the food we
eat didn't exist 200 years ago.

00:19:23.150 --> 00:19:26.160 align:middle line:84%
So is it any wonder that
we have this epidemic?

00:19:26.160 --> 00:19:28.880 align:middle line:84%
If you understand this idea
of inflammation and immunity

00:19:28.880 --> 00:19:31.730 align:middle line:84%
and defense and protection
and offending agents

00:19:31.730 --> 00:19:34.250 align:middle line:84%
and you understand that all
of this begins in the gut

00:19:34.250 --> 00:19:36.500 align:middle line:84%
and the gut is the interface
between the outside world

00:19:36.500 --> 00:19:38.240 align:middle line:84%
and the inside
world, you can see

00:19:38.240 --> 00:19:41.190 align:middle line:84%
how it all boils down to
what's happening right here.

00:19:41.190 --> 00:19:42.754 align:middle line:90%
Now, this is just physical.

00:19:42.754 --> 00:19:43.670 align:middle line:90%
This is just physical.

00:19:43.670 --> 00:19:44.960 align:middle line:90%
And there are other things, too.

00:19:44.960 --> 00:19:46.700 align:middle line:84%
Like you have to know
how to breathe correctly.

00:19:46.700 --> 00:19:48.158 align:middle line:84%
And you got to be
moving your body.

00:19:48.158 --> 00:19:50.570 align:middle line:84%
But for the most part, if
you want to do one thing,

00:19:50.570 --> 00:19:52.251 align:middle line:90%
slice through that Gordian knot.

00:19:52.251 --> 00:19:53.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You mentioned fasting.

00:19:53.500 --> 00:19:54.140 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: It's so important.

00:19:54.140 --> 00:19:55.681 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I want to
ask you about that.

00:19:55.681 --> 00:19:57.680 align:middle line:84%
Because if you like
slice the Gordian knot,

00:19:57.680 --> 00:19:59.639 align:middle line:84%
you're going to go right
to cleansing the body.

00:19:59.639 --> 00:20:01.221 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: It's the
best way to cleanse.

00:20:01.221 --> 00:20:03.590 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But the question
is, you mentioned that we

00:20:03.590 --> 00:20:05.730 align:middle line:90%
have this defense system.

00:20:05.730 --> 00:20:07.710 align:middle line:84%
And have you ever
done a long fast?

00:20:07.710 --> 00:20:08.510 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Yes.

00:20:08.510 --> 00:20:09.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Obviously.

00:20:09.630 --> 00:20:10.430 align:middle line:90%
Does your body--

00:20:10.430 --> 00:20:11.690 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Well, I don't
know, three-day fast.

00:20:11.690 --> 00:20:12.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Three days.

00:20:12.210 --> 00:20:13.020 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Some people
do 40-day fasts.

00:20:13.020 --> 00:20:14.811 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: In the beginning,
doesn't your body

00:20:14.811 --> 00:20:15.866 align:middle line:90%
tell you you need to eat?

00:20:15.866 --> 00:20:16.990 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: It's conditioning.

00:20:16.990 --> 00:20:17.790 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:20:17.790 --> 00:20:19.690 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: It's not necessary.

00:20:19.690 --> 00:20:22.040 align:middle line:90%
We eat way too much.

00:20:22.040 --> 00:20:23.810 align:middle line:84%
And every time
you eat, your body

00:20:23.810 --> 00:20:26.720 align:middle line:84%
is spending its resources
to process that food.

00:20:26.720 --> 00:20:29.221 align:middle line:84%
Eating is one of the hardest
things that the body has to do.

00:20:29.221 --> 00:20:31.178 align:middle line:84%
Of the things the body
does on a regular basis,

00:20:31.178 --> 00:20:33.780 align:middle line:84%
eating is probably the hardest
thing that the body has to do.

00:20:33.780 --> 00:20:36.280 align:middle line:84%
So that's why every study that's
ever been done on longevity

00:20:36.280 --> 00:20:38.540 align:middle line:84%
