00:39:29.240 --> 00:39:31.310 align:middle line:84%
Let's just go through, if
we can, really quickly.

00:39:31.310 --> 00:39:33.050 align:middle line:90%
Serotonin, SSRIs.

00:39:33.050 --> 00:39:34.934 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: OK, serotonin
gets the reputation

00:39:34.934 --> 00:39:36.350 align:middle line:84%
of being the happy
hormone, right?

00:39:36.350 --> 00:39:38.558 align:middle line:84%
If you're a layperson, you
think it's with happiness.

00:39:38.558 --> 00:39:39.680 align:middle line:90%
Not a happy hormone.

00:39:39.680 --> 00:39:41.480 align:middle line:90%
It's a vigilance hormone.

00:39:41.480 --> 00:39:43.740 align:middle line:90%
It's a daytime hormone.

00:39:43.740 --> 00:39:46.910 align:middle line:84%
It balances out or
antagonizes melatonin.

00:39:46.910 --> 00:39:49.120 align:middle line:84%
Serotonin and melatonin
are two of the same family.

00:39:49.120 --> 00:39:50.453 align:middle line:90%
And they balance each other out.

00:39:50.453 --> 00:39:52.630 align:middle line:84%
And serotonin is a very,
very primitive hormone.

00:39:52.630 --> 00:39:53.840 align:middle line:90%
Yeast have serotonin.

00:39:53.840 --> 00:39:55.230 align:middle line:90%
Bacteria has serotonin.

00:39:55.230 --> 00:39:59.270 align:middle line:84%
So serotonin is an
awareness hormone.

00:39:59.270 --> 00:40:01.640 align:middle line:84%
It helps you handle the
vicissitudes, the ups and downs

00:40:01.640 --> 00:40:04.624 align:middle line:84%
of life, the ups and downs
of being in daily life.

00:40:04.624 --> 00:40:07.040 align:middle line:84%
During the daytime, there's
all kinds of things happening.

00:40:07.040 --> 00:40:08.090 align:middle line:84%
Sleep, you don't have
to worry about it.

00:40:08.090 --> 00:40:09.270 align:middle line:84%
Sleep, you're growing,
you're repairing.

00:40:09.270 --> 00:40:09.590 align:middle line:90%
You're chill.

00:40:09.590 --> 00:40:10.160 align:middle line:90%
You're at night.

00:40:10.160 --> 00:40:11.180 align:middle line:90%
Nothing's happening.

00:40:11.180 --> 00:40:12.731 align:middle line:84%
But in the day, you
need to be aware.

00:40:12.731 --> 00:40:13.730 align:middle line:90%
You need to be vigilant.

00:40:13.730 --> 00:40:15.650 align:middle line:84%
Most serotonin in your
body is not your brain.

00:40:15.650 --> 00:40:17.270 align:middle line:90%
It's in your digestive system.

00:40:17.270 --> 00:40:18.840 align:middle line:90%
Why your digestive system?

00:40:18.840 --> 00:40:20.890 align:middle line:84%
Why would serotonin, which
is a vigilance hormone

00:40:20.890 --> 00:40:22.130 align:middle line:84%
and an awareness
hormone, why would it

00:40:22.130 --> 00:40:23.530 align:middle line:90%
be in your digestive system?

00:40:23.530 --> 00:40:26.790 align:middle line:84%
Because your digestive system
is in the greatest battle

00:40:26.790 --> 00:40:28.040 align:middle line:90%
there is with the environment.

00:40:28.040 --> 00:40:29.690 align:middle line:84%
Because you're
constantly eating.

00:40:29.690 --> 00:40:31.250 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's why they
call it the gut-brain.

00:40:31.250 --> 00:40:32.916 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: It's called
the gut-brain axis.

00:40:32.916 --> 00:40:34.407 align:middle line:90%
But this is the core of it.

00:40:34.407 --> 00:40:35.990 align:middle line:84%
You know, our brain
here is important.

00:40:35.990 --> 00:40:38.630 align:middle line:84%
But the brain here
is interpreting

00:40:38.630 --> 00:40:40.030 align:middle line:90%
the environment via the food.

00:40:40.030 --> 00:40:41.667 align:middle line:84%
So serotonin is a
digestive hormone

00:40:41.667 --> 00:40:43.000 align:middle line:90%
more than it is a brain hormone.

00:40:43.000 --> 00:40:43.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:40:43.950 --> 00:40:45.470 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Vastly,
not a little bit,

00:40:45.470 --> 00:40:47.990 align:middle line:84%
like 97% of the
serotonin in your body

00:40:47.990 --> 00:40:49.770 align:middle line:90%
is in your digestive tract.

00:40:49.770 --> 00:40:52.280 align:middle line:84%
So it's a digestive hormone
because the digestive system

00:40:52.280 --> 00:40:54.110 align:middle line:90%
needs this vigilance aspect.

00:40:54.110 --> 00:40:56.660 align:middle line:84%
So SSRIs are a
recipe for disaster.

00:40:56.660 --> 00:40:58.220 align:middle line:90%
Now, if somebody is depressed--

00:40:58.220 --> 00:41:00.659 align:middle line:84%
And I've done talks where
I've talked about SSRIs

00:41:00.659 --> 00:41:01.700 align:middle line:90%
and it being problematic.

00:41:01.700 --> 00:41:05.359 align:middle line:84%
But if somebody is depressed,
it's hard to say to them,

00:41:05.359 --> 00:41:07.150 align:middle line:84%
don't take your Zoloft
or don't take your--

00:41:07.150 --> 00:41:08.270 align:middle line:84%
I mean, "I'm gonna kill myself
if I don't have my Zoloft."

00:41:08.270 --> 00:41:09.070 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:41:09.070 --> 00:41:11.840 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: So, you know, I think
everybody's number-one health

00:41:11.840 --> 00:41:14.060 align:middle line:84%
goal should be to wean
themselves off of it.

00:41:14.060 --> 00:41:15.680 align:middle line:84%
But you can't say
that to somebody

00:41:15.680 --> 00:41:17.932 align:middle line:84%
who's got mental health
issues and these things

00:41:17.932 --> 00:41:19.140 align:middle line:90%
are somehow stabilizing them.

00:41:19.140 --> 00:41:21.320 align:middle line:84%
However, what you
can do is you can

00:41:21.320 --> 00:41:24.770 align:middle line:84%
start to create other avenues to
approach the health challenge.

00:41:24.770 --> 00:41:27.770 align:middle line:84%
So for depression,
you can do movement.

00:41:27.770 --> 00:41:30.080 align:middle line:84%
That's a great way to
up-regulate happy hormones

00:41:30.080 --> 00:41:32.100 align:middle line:84%
in the brain, not
serotonin, necessarily,

00:41:32.100 --> 00:41:33.892 align:middle line:90%
but dopamine and norepinephrine.

00:41:33.892 --> 00:41:34.850 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Norepinephrine.

00:41:34.850 --> 00:41:35.570 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Exactly.

00:41:35.570 --> 00:41:37.140 align:middle line:84%
So movement is a
very important thing

00:41:37.140 --> 00:41:38.360 align:middle line:84%
if you're dealing
with depression.

00:41:38.360 --> 00:41:39.770 align:middle line:84%
Foods, of course, are
a very important thing.

00:41:39.770 --> 00:41:41.365 align:middle line:84%
Keeping your blood sugar
stable is important.

00:41:41.365 --> 00:41:42.865 align:middle line:84%
There are nutrients
that you can do.

00:41:42.865 --> 00:41:44.990 align:middle line:84%
So I'm always hesitant
to say to somebody,

00:41:44.990 --> 00:41:47.490 align:middle line:84%
don't take your Zoloft or
don't take your Effexor.

00:41:47.490 --> 00:41:49.569 align:middle line:84%
But what I prefer
to say is, maybe

00:41:49.569 --> 00:41:51.110 align:middle line:84%
there's other things
that you can do,

00:41:51.110 --> 00:41:52.967 align:middle line:84%
if you so desire,
to wean yourself

00:41:52.967 --> 00:41:54.300 align:middle line:90%
off your Effexor or your Zoloft.

00:41:54.300 --> 00:41:57.320 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You covered a
little bit of the SSRI.

00:41:57.320 --> 00:41:58.420 align:middle line:90%
And now the--

00:41:58.420 --> 00:41:58.670 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Thyroid?

00:41:58.670 --> 00:41:59.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --whole thyroid, yeah.

00:41:59.480 --> 00:42:00.410 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: The thyroid thing.

00:42:00.410 --> 00:42:02.035 align:middle line:84%
Here's the thing
about the thyroid, OK.

00:42:02.035 --> 00:42:04.190 align:middle line:84%
And it always amazes me
that the thyroid medicine

00:42:04.190 --> 00:42:05.300 align:middle line:84%
is like the number
three or number four

00:42:05.300 --> 00:42:06.133 align:middle line:90%
medicine every year.

00:42:06.133 --> 00:42:08.717 align:middle line:84%
Because every pharmacist knows
they're the most useless drugs.

00:42:08.717 --> 00:42:10.550 align:middle line:84%
And this is why people
on thyroid medication

00:42:10.550 --> 00:42:12.160 align:middle line:84%
have to keep
changing their dose.

00:42:12.160 --> 00:42:13.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Tell us why.

00:42:13.040 --> 00:42:15.350 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Because you
can't control the thyroid

00:42:15.350 --> 00:42:17.870 align:middle line:84%
without controlling
the preceding organs.

00:42:17.870 --> 00:42:21.080 align:middle line:84%
The thyroid is a secondary
system in the sense

00:42:21.080 --> 00:42:24.470 align:middle line:84%
that it's reflective of what's
happening in the blood sugar

00:42:24.470 --> 00:42:28.349 align:middle line:84%
system, specifically the stress
system, the blood sugar system,

00:42:28.349 --> 00:42:29.390 align:middle line:90%
and the digestive system.

00:42:29.390 --> 00:42:31.460 align:middle line:84%
I call this the
triangle of disease.

00:42:31.460 --> 00:42:33.680 align:middle line:84%
There are three points
of bodily breakdown

00:42:33.680 --> 00:42:35.757 align:middle line:84%
that underlie all
disease states.

00:42:35.757 --> 00:42:37.340 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
digestive system, which

00:42:37.340 --> 00:42:40.100 align:middle line:84%
we've talked about, and then
the blood sugar system, and then

00:42:40.100 --> 00:42:42.650 align:middle line:84%
the body's stress
management system.

00:42:42.650 --> 00:42:44.750 align:middle line:84%
The thyroid is
reflective of what's

00:42:44.750 --> 00:42:46.550 align:middle line:84%
happening at those
three levels so

00:42:46.550 --> 00:42:49.520 align:middle line:84%
that when your cortisol, your
body's stress hormone, is high,

00:42:49.520 --> 00:42:52.850 align:middle line:84%
your body will compensate by
slowing down thyroid function.

00:42:52.850 --> 00:42:54.287 align:middle line:84%
When your blood
sugar is messed up

00:42:54.287 --> 00:42:56.120 align:middle line:84%
and when your digestive
system is messed up,

00:42:56.120 --> 00:42:57.720 align:middle line:84%
likewise, your thyroid
will slow down.

00:42:57.720 --> 00:43:01.130 align:middle line:84%
So to try to approach the
thyroid by itself by giving

00:43:01.130 --> 00:43:03.210 align:middle line:90%
hormones is not going to work.

00:43:03.210 --> 00:43:05.300 align:middle line:84%
Because the problem is
not at the thyroid level.

00:43:05.300 --> 00:43:07.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So then how do you
regulate the blood sugar?

00:43:07.190 --> 00:43:08.960 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Well, you want to
work with the triangle, first

00:43:08.960 --> 00:43:09.170 align:middle line:90%
of all.

00:43:09.170 --> 00:43:09.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:43:09.540 --> 00:43:11.260 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: And so the triangle
means work with cortisol.

00:43:11.260 --> 00:43:11.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:43:11.870 --> 00:43:13.953 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: First and foremost,
slow, deep breathing.

00:43:13.953 --> 00:43:15.150 align:middle line:90%
Relax the body.

00:43:15.150 --> 00:43:15.520 align:middle line:90%
Make sure you're not putting--

00:43:15.520 --> 00:43:16.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Parasympathetic
nervous system.

00:43:16.970 --> 00:43:18.440 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: That's where the
parasympathetic nervous

00:43:18.440 --> 00:43:20.648 align:middle line:84%
system-- activate the
parasympathetic nervous system.

00:43:20.648 --> 00:43:21.502 align:middle line:90%
Take a hot shower.

00:43:21.502 --> 00:43:22.710 align:middle line:90%
We talked about that earlier.

00:43:22.710 --> 00:43:25.010 align:middle line:90%
If you can sit in a bath.

00:43:25.010 --> 00:43:27.510 align:middle line:84%
Simply that alone will activate
the parasympathetic nervous

00:43:27.510 --> 00:43:28.310 align:middle line:90%
system.

00:43:28.310 --> 00:43:31.070 align:middle line:84%
Gratitude activates the
parasympathetic nervous system.

00:43:31.070 --> 00:43:33.890 align:middle line:84%
Love activates the
parasympathetic nervous system.

00:43:33.890 --> 00:43:37.086 align:middle line:84%
Bodily relaxation activates the
parasympathetic nervous system.

00:43:37.086 --> 00:43:39.710 align:middle line:84%
Anything you do to activate the
parasympathetic nervous system.

00:43:39.710 --> 00:43:40.859 align:middle line:90%
That's step number one.

00:43:40.859 --> 00:43:42.900 align:middle line:84%
Step number two is you
stabilize the blood sugar.

00:43:42.900 --> 00:43:44.850 align:middle line:84%
Really, when you talk about
stabilizing the blood sugar,

00:43:44.850 --> 00:43:46.225 align:middle line:84%
the most important
aspect of that

00:43:46.225 --> 00:43:49.940 align:middle line:84%
is keeping your insulin low,
keeping your insulin sharp so

00:43:49.940 --> 00:43:53.660 align:middle line:84%
that your cells are all
responsive to insulin.

00:43:53.660 --> 00:43:55.100 align:middle line:84%
The biggest disease
on the planet

00:43:55.100 --> 00:43:57.180 align:middle line:84%
that's behind heart
disease and behind cancer,

00:43:57.180 --> 00:43:59.510 align:middle line:84%
which is supposedly
the first two diseases,

00:43:59.510 --> 00:44:02.300 align:middle line:84%
is diabetes or
insulin resistance.

00:44:02.300 --> 00:44:04.770 align:middle line:84%
Not type one diabetes,
but type two diabetes,

00:44:04.770 --> 00:44:05.937 align:middle line:90%
which is insulin resistance.

00:44:05.937 --> 00:44:07.561 align:middle line:84%
So what you want to
do is you want make

00:44:07.561 --> 00:44:08.720 align:middle line:90%
your insulin really strong.

00:44:08.720 --> 00:44:10.670 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So insulin regulates
the blood sugar, right?

00:44:10.670 --> 00:44:12.170 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Insulin regulates
the blood sugar, correct.

00:44:12.170 --> 00:44:14.310 align:middle line:84%
When you eat sugar,
your insulin goes up.

00:44:14.310 --> 00:44:16.690 align:middle line:84%
And then the job of
insulin is to open up cells

00:44:16.690 --> 00:44:18.650 align:middle line:84%
so sugar can get
stashed into the cells.

00:44:18.650 --> 00:44:20.360 align:middle line:90%
Then your blood sugar goes down.

00:44:20.360 --> 00:44:21.280 align:middle line:90%
And then you eat more.

00:44:21.280 --> 00:44:22.280 align:middle line:90%
So your insulin goes up.

00:44:22.280 --> 00:44:24.230 align:middle line:84%
And then your blood sugar
gets, your sugar gets--

00:44:24.230 --> 00:44:25.646 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How do you
keep it active?

00:44:25.646 --> 00:44:26.900 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: You sensitize it.

00:44:26.900 --> 00:44:29.326 align:middle line:84%
You want to make your
cells sensitive to insulin.

00:44:29.326 --> 00:44:30.950 align:middle line:84%
You do it by keeping
your insulin down.

00:44:30.950 --> 00:44:31.750 align:middle line:90%
It's kind of like--

00:44:31.750 --> 00:44:32.619 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: How?

00:44:32.619 --> 00:44:34.160 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Did you
ever go to a concert

00:44:34.160 --> 00:44:37.430 align:middle line:84%
where the music is really
loud and, gradually, it

00:44:37.430 --> 00:44:38.800 align:middle line:90%
doesn't seem as loud anymore?

00:44:38.800 --> 00:44:39.800 align:middle line:90%
Your body adjusts to it.

00:44:39.800 --> 00:44:41.840 align:middle line:84%
It turns the volume
down on the music.

00:44:41.840 --> 00:44:43.940 align:middle line:84%
And this is one of the
ways the body works.

00:44:43.940 --> 00:44:45.350 align:middle line:90%
It's a compensatory mechanism.

00:44:45.350 --> 00:44:47.005 align:middle line:84%
So over the course
of time when insulin

00:44:47.005 --> 00:44:48.880 align:middle line:84%
is kind of going up and
down and up and down,

00:44:48.880 --> 00:44:50.810 align:middle line:84%
a lot of this insulin present,
the cells lose their ability

00:44:50.810 --> 00:44:51.880 align:middle line:90%
to sense insulin.

00:44:51.880 --> 00:44:53.165 align:middle line:90%
They become insulin resistant.

00:44:53.165 --> 00:44:54.290 align:middle line:90%
So what does that tell you?

00:44:54.290 --> 00:44:56.540 align:middle line:84%
If you want to resensitize
your body to insulin,

00:44:56.540 --> 00:44:57.980 align:middle line:90%
lower your insulin.

00:44:57.980 --> 00:45:00.200 align:middle line:84%
And this is why fasting
is so important.

00:45:00.200 --> 00:45:01.001 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Again.

00:45:01.001 --> 00:45:02.249 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Again, again fasting.

00:45:02.249 --> 00:45:04.160 align:middle line:84%
And if you don't want
to fast, reducing foods

00:45:04.160 --> 00:45:05.660 align:middle line:90%
that spike your insulin.

00:45:05.660 --> 00:45:07.520 align:middle line:84%
The most important
insulin-spiking foods are

00:45:07.520 --> 00:45:09.365 align:middle line:84%
the foods we all
love, the breads--

00:45:09.365 --> 00:45:09.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Carbohydrates.

00:45:09.650 --> 00:45:11.270 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: --and the
grains, the carbohydrates

00:45:11.270 --> 00:45:12.520 align:middle line:90%
and the sweets and the sugar.

00:45:12.520 --> 00:45:14.911 align:middle line:84%
And today, you can't go 30
feet without finding a source

00:45:14.911 --> 00:45:15.910 align:middle line:90%
of these kinds of foods.

00:45:15.910 --> 00:45:16.710 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:45:16.710 --> 00:45:19.400 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: And if you are
in a state of low reward,

00:45:19.400 --> 00:45:21.740 align:middle line:84%
low dopamine-- because
sugar, calories,

00:45:21.740 --> 00:45:23.524 align:middle line:84%
and carbs are
attached to reward.

00:45:23.524 --> 00:45:25.190 align:middle line:84%
And you're constantly
looking for reward

00:45:25.190 --> 00:45:27.140 align:middle line:84%
because you don't have
reward in your life.

00:45:27.140 --> 00:45:29.180 align:middle line:84%
Because you ever notice how,
and I don't if you noticed this,

00:45:29.180 --> 00:45:30.590 align:middle line:84%
but when you're in
love, you don't eat.

00:45:30.590 --> 00:45:31.070 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hm.

00:45:31.070 --> 00:45:31.700 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Right?

00:45:31.700 --> 00:45:33.460 align:middle line:84%
You know that kind of
myth or meme about--

00:45:33.460 --> 00:45:34.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Constant dopamine rush.

00:45:34.550 --> 00:45:35.780 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: You constantly
are in reward.

00:45:35.780 --> 00:45:36.860 align:middle line:90%
You already have the reward.

00:45:36.860 --> 00:45:36.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:45:36.980 --> 00:45:39.438 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: When you have reward
going, you don't need to eat.

00:45:39.438 --> 00:45:43.670 align:middle line:84%
So get reward somewhere
else is one of the best ways

00:45:43.670 --> 00:45:45.530 align:middle line:84%
to resensitize
yourselves to insulin.

00:45:45.530 --> 00:45:48.000 align:middle line:84%
But in general, keeping
your carbs down.

00:45:48.000 --> 00:45:49.820 align:middle line:84%
Going ketogenic is a
great strategy, too.

00:45:49.820 --> 00:45:51.434 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So proteins,
rich greens--

00:45:51.434 --> 00:45:53.100 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Proteins get
turned into sugar.

00:45:53.100 --> 00:45:53.740 align:middle line:90%
So you got to be--

00:45:53.740 --> 00:45:54.290 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: They do?

00:45:54.290 --> 00:45:55.700 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Yeah, very quickly.

00:45:55.700 --> 00:45:56.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Proteins
get turned to sugar?

00:45:56.240 --> 00:45:57.240 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Yes, very quickly.

00:45:57.240 --> 00:45:58.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I thought carbs
got turned into sugar.

00:45:58.220 --> 00:45:58.610 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: They do.

00:45:58.610 --> 00:45:59.540 align:middle line:90%
Carbs are sugar.

00:45:59.540 --> 00:45:59.830 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:45:59.830 --> 00:46:01.538 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: And carbs
break down into sugar.

00:46:01.538 --> 00:46:03.440 align:middle line:84%
But protein, the
body is very clever.

00:46:03.440 --> 00:46:05.570 align:middle line:84%
And it can efficiently,
quite efficiently

00:46:05.570 --> 00:46:08.422 align:middle line:84%
actually, turn
protein into sugar.

00:46:08.422 --> 00:46:10.130 align:middle line:84%
So if you're eating--
and a lot of people

00:46:10.130 --> 00:46:11.630 align:middle line:84%
make this mistake
when they go paleo

00:46:11.630 --> 00:46:13.463 align:middle line:84%
or they eat a lot of
protein, is they think,

00:46:13.463 --> 00:46:14.840 align:middle line:84%
oh, I'll just eat
a lot of steak.

00:46:14.840 --> 00:46:15.730 align:middle line:90%
And they don't lose weight.

00:46:15.730 --> 00:46:16.880 align:middle line:84%
And they can't figure out
why I'm not losing weight.

00:46:16.880 --> 00:46:18.920 align:middle line:84%
Because your body is turning
that protein into sugar,

00:46:18.920 --> 00:46:19.940 align:middle line:90%
which ends up as fat.

00:46:19.940 --> 00:46:21.740 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Is the body going
to turn anything into sugar

00:46:21.740 --> 00:46:22.870 align:middle line:90%
if you don't give it sugar?

00:46:22.870 --> 00:46:23.740 align:middle line:90%
Because it needs--

00:46:23.740 --> 00:46:24.620 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Um, yes.

00:46:24.620 --> 00:46:24.710 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: glycogen.

00:46:24.710 --> 00:46:25.100 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: No, no.

00:46:25.100 --> 00:46:26.000 align:middle line:90%
Because it can burn fat.

00:46:26.000 --> 00:46:27.500 align:middle line:84%
That's what the
ketogenic diet is.

00:46:27.500 --> 00:46:27.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:46:27.740 --> 00:46:28.906 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: So it can burn fat.

00:46:28.906 --> 00:46:31.610 align:middle line:84%
And your goal is to be fat
burner, not a sugar burner.

00:46:31.610 --> 00:46:33.740 align:middle line:84%
Fat is a much cleaner, more
dense source of energy.

00:46:33.740 --> 00:46:36.323 align:middle line:84%
This is why the ketogenic diet
is so helpful and so important.

00:46:36.323 --> 00:46:37.760 align:middle line:90%
Because it's a fat-burning diet.

00:46:37.760 --> 00:46:39.260 align:middle line:84%
So you want to
encourage the body

00:46:39.260 --> 00:46:41.474 align:middle line:84%
to get its energy from
fat as much as possible.

00:46:41.474 --> 00:46:43.640 align:middle line:84%
And the way you do that is
by keeping your carbs out

00:46:43.640 --> 00:46:45.410 align:middle line:84%
as best as possible and
keeping your protein low.

00:46:45.410 --> 00:46:46.890 align:middle line:84%
You need protein
for other things.

00:46:46.890 --> 00:46:48.140 align:middle line:84%
So you got have some
amount of protein.

00:46:48.140 --> 00:46:49.806 align:middle line:84%
But keeping the carbs
down to a minimum.

00:46:49.806 --> 00:46:51.390 align:middle line:90%
There's no real need for carbs.

00:46:51.390 --> 00:46:52.910 align:middle line:84%
You need fat and
you need protein.

00:46:52.910 --> 00:46:54.440 align:middle line:84%
But there's no real
need for carbs.

00:46:54.440 --> 00:46:56.030 align:middle line:84%
Now, I'm not saying
go to zero carb.

00:46:56.030 --> 00:46:57.980 align:middle line:84%
Because carbs are a
good source of energy.

00:46:57.980 --> 00:46:59.900 align:middle line:84%
And there's
phytonutrients and things

00:46:59.900 --> 00:47:01.020 align:middle line:90%
associated with the carbs.

00:47:01.020 --> 00:47:03.270 align:middle line:84%
So that's the second point
of the triangle of disease,

00:47:03.270 --> 00:47:04.400 align:middle line:90%
is the blood sugar.

00:47:04.400 --> 00:47:06.000 align:middle line:84%
And then the third point
is the digestive system.

00:47:06.000 --> 00:47:07.370 align:middle line:84%
But here's where it
gets really interesting.

00:47:07.370 --> 00:47:08.240 align:middle line:90%
So you got a triangle, right?

00:47:08.240 --> 00:47:10.531 align:middle line:84%
Digestion, which breaks down
woefully early by the way,

00:47:10.531 --> 00:47:13.790 align:middle line:84%
like in the womb or at birth
or within the first year

00:47:13.790 --> 00:47:16.380 align:middle line:84%
of the child's life his
or her digestive system

00:47:16.380 --> 00:47:17.180 align:middle line:90%
is breaking down.

00:47:17.180 --> 00:47:18.260 align:middle line:90%
That's what colic is.

00:47:18.260 --> 00:47:20.690 align:middle line:84%
Colic is the digestive system
starting to break down.

00:47:20.690 --> 00:47:22.895 align:middle line:84%
Eczema, pimples,
there's all these things

00:47:22.895 --> 00:47:24.800 align:middle line:84%
that happen to kids
are manifestations

00:47:24.800 --> 00:47:26.390 align:middle line:84%
of the digestive
system breaking down.

00:47:26.390 --> 00:47:27.290 align:middle line:90%
That's a whole other story.

00:47:27.290 --> 00:47:27.710 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:47:27.710 --> 00:47:28.980 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: But here's
where it gets cool.

00:47:28.980 --> 00:47:31.010 align:middle line:84%
So the digestive system,
when it breaks down,

00:47:31.010 --> 00:47:32.480 align:middle line:84%
it creates changes
in blood sugar.

00:47:32.480 --> 00:47:35.220 align:middle line:84%
Diabetes has behind it
digestive issues, by the way.

00:47:35.220 --> 00:47:36.158 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:47:36.158 --> 00:47:38.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hm, everything does.

00:47:38.060 --> 00:47:38.420 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Everything does.

00:47:38.420 --> 00:47:39.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's all going back to--

00:47:39.110 --> 00:47:39.330 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Everything does.

00:47:39.330 --> 00:47:39.690 align:middle line:90%
That's what I'm telling you.

00:47:39.690 --> 00:47:40.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I see what
you're saying.

00:47:40.220 --> 00:47:41.180 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: And then
you go into cortisol.

00:47:41.180 --> 00:47:42.440 align:middle line:84%
But here's where it
gets interesting.

00:47:42.440 --> 00:47:44.740 align:middle line:84%
So the cortisol spikes and
that will cause your thyroid

00:47:44.740 --> 00:47:46.174 align:middle line:90%
to slow down.

00:47:46.174 --> 00:47:47.840 align:middle line:84%
But here's where it
becomes interesting.

00:47:47.840 --> 00:47:50.385 align:middle line:84%
The thyroid regulates
the digestive system.

00:47:50.385 --> 00:47:52.010 align:middle line:84%
So when the thyroid
slows down, now you

00:47:52.010 --> 00:47:54.140 align:middle line:84%
have even slower
digestive functioning--

00:47:54.140 --> 00:47:54.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:47:54.470 --> 00:47:55.850 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: --which leads to more
blood sugar problems, which

00:47:55.850 --> 00:47:57.130 align:middle line:90%
leads to more cortisol.

00:47:57.130 --> 00:47:59.120 align:middle line:84%
And you get this
downward spiral.

00:47:59.120 --> 00:48:01.760 align:middle line:84%
And most people are in this
from birth until the time

00:48:01.760 --> 00:48:04.610 align:middle line:84%
that their disease hits
at the age of 30 or 40.

00:48:04.610 --> 00:48:06.264 align:middle line:84%
And this is all
percolating underneath.

00:48:06.264 --> 00:48:08.930 align:middle line:84%
And people are like, well, I was
just sitting there watching TV,

00:48:08.930 --> 00:48:11.840 align:middle line:84%
minding my own business, and
all of a sudden, I got cancer.

00:48:11.840 --> 00:48:13.460 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
I got arthritis.

00:48:13.460 --> 00:48:15.230 align:middle line:84%
And all of sudden, I
got hypothyroidism.

00:48:15.230 --> 00:48:17.229 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden, I
got these disease states,

00:48:17.229 --> 00:48:18.860 align:middle line:84%
not knowing that
this triangle has

00:48:18.860 --> 00:48:22.220 align:middle line:84%
been in effect their entire life
where the digestive system is

00:48:22.220 --> 00:48:23.020 align:middle line:90%
broken down.

00:48:23.020 --> 00:48:25.311 align:middle line:84%
And the blood sugar system
is starting to lose control.

00:48:25.311 --> 00:48:28.340 align:middle line:84%
And you're chronically
spiking cortisol.

00:48:28.340 --> 00:48:29.950 align:middle line:90%
Your thyroid is slowing down.

00:48:29.950 --> 00:48:31.410 align:middle line:90%
And this whole thing happens.

00:48:31.410 --> 00:48:33.830 align:middle line:84%
By the way, behind
all disease states,

00:48:33.830 --> 00:48:35.959 align:middle line:84%
you'll find this
triangle of disease

00:48:35.959 --> 00:48:37.250 align:middle line:90%
and you'll find hypothyroidism.

00:48:37.250 --> 00:48:40.820 align:middle line:84%
And you don't need
a thyroid test.

00:48:40.820 --> 00:48:43.130 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to waste your
time with a thyroid test.

00:48:43.130 --> 00:48:44.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Just go
right towards this.

