>>FUCHS: And we all
have that voice.

00:51:48.869 --> 00:51:50.535 align:middle line:84%
And that voice is
always talking to you.

00:51:50.535 --> 00:51:52.170 align:middle line:84%
And it will tell you to
turn left at the corner

00:51:52.170 --> 00:51:53.160 align:middle line:90%
or right at the corner.

00:51:53.160 --> 00:51:53.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah, that's true.

00:51:53.970 --> 00:51:54.803 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Everything.

00:51:54.803 --> 00:51:56.700 align:middle line:84%
And it's called the
still, small voice.

00:51:56.700 --> 00:51:58.020 align:middle line:90%
And it's been known about.

00:51:58.020 --> 00:51:59.520 align:middle line:84%
And this voice has
been known about.

00:51:59.520 --> 00:52:02.222 align:middle line:84%
And it's almost like, you can
give it a Christian metaphor.

00:52:02.222 --> 00:52:03.180 align:middle line:90%
You can say it's Jesus.

00:52:03.180 --> 00:52:04.050 align:middle line:90%
You can say it's God.

00:52:04.050 --> 00:52:05.133 align:middle line:90%
You could say it's spirit.

00:52:05.133 --> 00:52:06.530 align:middle line:90%
You could say whatever it is.

00:52:06.530 --> 00:52:08.130 align:middle line:90%
And we don't listen.

00:52:08.130 --> 00:52:09.330 align:middle line:90%
And that's the one thing.

00:52:09.330 --> 00:52:11.280 align:middle line:84%
The body has a
wisdom built into it

00:52:11.280 --> 00:52:13.042 align:middle line:90%
that it wants to share with us.

00:52:13.042 --> 00:52:15.000 align:middle line:84%
And it will tell us
everything we need to know.

00:52:15.000 --> 00:52:17.220 align:middle line:84%
So that's even before we
get into what you can do.

00:52:17.220 --> 00:52:18.860 align:middle line:90%
Number one, listen to your body.

00:52:18.860 --> 00:52:21.550 align:middle line:84%
So then, specifically,
listen for foods.

00:52:21.550 --> 00:52:23.670 align:middle line:84%
Stay away from foods
that are problematic.

00:52:23.670 --> 00:52:25.586 align:middle line:84%
If a food makes you feel
tired, don't eat it.

00:52:25.586 --> 00:52:27.210 align:middle line:84%
If a food is associated
with-- and then

00:52:27.210 --> 00:52:29.760 align:middle line:84%
see how you feel
after you eat a food.

00:52:29.760 --> 00:52:31.860 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's one thing
to say if a food makes

00:52:31.860 --> 00:52:33.068 align:middle line:90%
you feel tired, don't eat it.

00:52:33.068 --> 00:52:33.902 align:middle line:90%
But at least notice.

00:52:33.902 --> 00:52:35.318 align:middle line:84%
Even before you
decide not to eat,

00:52:35.318 --> 00:52:37.440 align:middle line:84%
at least notice that after
you eat a certain food,

00:52:37.440 --> 00:52:38.310 align:middle line:90%
you're tired.

00:52:38.310 --> 00:52:40.140 align:middle line:84%
Or after you eat a certain
food, you get a rash.

00:52:40.140 --> 00:52:41.580 align:middle line:84%
Or after you eat
a certain food--

00:52:41.580 --> 00:52:42.410 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:52:42.410 --> 00:52:43.630 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: --your blood
pressure goes up.

00:52:43.630 --> 00:52:46.130 align:middle line:84%
Or after eat a certain food,
you don't feel good in any way.

00:52:46.130 --> 00:52:47.307 align:middle line:90%
Pay attention.

00:52:47.307 --> 00:52:48.390 align:middle line:90%
Lay off the problem foods.

00:52:48.390 --> 00:52:49.190 align:middle line:90%
That's number one.

00:52:49.190 --> 00:52:50.250 align:middle line:90%
And eat less food.

00:52:50.250 --> 00:52:53.220 align:middle line:84%
Number two, don't
spike your blood sugar.

00:52:53.220 --> 00:52:55.530 align:middle line:84%
Try to stay with
foods that don't

00:52:55.530 --> 00:52:56.790 align:middle line:90%
make your blood sugar go up.

00:52:56.790 --> 00:52:58.980 align:middle line:84%
And eat foods that help
control your blood sugar

00:52:58.980 --> 00:53:00.360 align:middle line:90%
like fiber foods.

00:53:00.360 --> 00:53:02.130 align:middle line:84%
Foods that have a
lot of fiber in them

00:53:02.130 --> 00:53:03.630 align:middle line:84%
will keep your
blood sugar stable.

00:53:03.630 --> 00:53:05.280 align:middle line:84%
Stay away from fruit
juices or foods

00:53:05.280 --> 00:53:07.440 align:middle line:84%
that have super-high
concentrations of sugar

00:53:07.440 --> 00:53:09.270 align:middle line:84%
without the fiber,
processed foods.

00:53:09.270 --> 00:53:10.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Coffee not a thing?

00:53:10.650 --> 00:53:13.320 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: I don't want to get
into like yes, no, good, bad.

00:53:13.320 --> 00:53:13.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:53:13.680 --> 00:53:15.900 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Because, you know,
I don't feel comfortable

00:53:15.900 --> 00:53:18.150 align:middle line:84%
saying this is a good food
and this is a bad food.

00:53:18.150 --> 00:53:20.700 align:middle line:90%
Whatever you feel right for you.

00:53:20.700 --> 00:53:21.669 align:middle line:90%
But just listen.

00:53:21.669 --> 00:53:23.460 align:middle line:84%
Stay away from things
that cause your blood

00:53:23.460 --> 00:53:24.330 align:middle line:90%
sugar to go up and down.

00:53:24.330 --> 00:53:26.204 align:middle line:84%
And you'll know blood
sugar drops by fatigue.

00:53:26.204 --> 00:53:30.300 align:middle line:84%
You'll know blood sugar gets
too high by jittery and anxiety.

00:53:30.300 --> 00:53:32.130 align:middle line:84%
Number three, and maybe
the most important,

00:53:32.130 --> 00:53:35.100 align:middle line:84%
because we can do this right
away, lower your cortisol.

00:53:35.100 --> 00:53:38.160 align:middle line:84%
Do all the things you could
do to relax your body.

00:53:38.160 --> 00:53:40.140 align:middle line:90%
Number four, move your body.

00:53:40.140 --> 00:53:41.490 align:middle line:90%
Move the lymphatic system.

00:53:41.490 --> 00:53:43.530 align:middle line:84%
The body loves quick
bursts of movement followed

00:53:43.530 --> 00:53:45.720 align:middle line:90%
by long, luscious rest.

00:53:45.720 --> 00:53:47.550 align:middle line:90%
We don't mind working.

00:53:47.550 --> 00:53:49.170 align:middle line:84%
We just want to
work all the time.

00:53:49.170 --> 00:53:49.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:53:49.390 --> 00:53:50.870 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Because the
body likes to work.

00:53:50.870 --> 00:53:51.240 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It does.

00:53:51.240 --> 00:53:53.050 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: It just doesn't
want to work all the time.

00:53:53.050 --> 00:53:54.040 align:middle line:90%
And it doesn't need a lot.

00:53:54.040 --> 00:53:55.350 align:middle line:84%
It needs five
minutes of intensity.

00:53:55.350 --> 00:53:57.058 align:middle line:84%
And the best way to
exercise, by the way,

00:53:57.058 --> 00:53:59.555 align:middle line:84%
is intense exercise
for five minutes a day.

00:53:59.555 --> 00:54:01.180 align:middle line:84%
Which is kind of
cool, because then you

00:54:01.180 --> 00:54:02.420 align:middle line:90%
have a lot more time to rest.

00:54:02.420 --> 00:54:03.548 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to stay
in the gym for an hour

00:54:03.548 --> 00:54:03.740 align:middle line:90%
or half an hour.

00:54:03.740 --> 00:54:04.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's great.

00:54:04.310 --> 00:54:04.670 align:middle line:90%
That's it?

00:54:04.670 --> 00:54:04.925 align:middle line:90%
Five minutes?

00:54:04.925 --> 00:54:06.091 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Five minutes a day.

00:54:06.091 --> 00:54:08.220 align:middle line:84%
If you could do five minutes
a day everyday, great.

00:54:08.220 --> 00:54:09.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Of burst exercise?

00:54:09.470 --> 00:54:10.280 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Intense.

00:54:10.280 --> 00:54:12.530 align:middle line:84%
And you know it's exercise
because your body is saying

00:54:12.530 --> 00:54:14.580 align:middle line:90%
we don't need to do this.

00:54:14.580 --> 00:54:15.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Stop.

00:54:15.380 --> 00:54:15.720 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Right.

00:54:15.720 --> 00:54:17.300 align:middle line:84%
Your body is saying we
don't need to do this.

00:54:17.300 --> 00:54:18.446 align:middle line:90%
It's not even your body.

00:54:18.446 --> 00:54:20.695 align:middle line:84%
It's your mind that's saying
we don't need to do this.

00:54:20.695 --> 00:54:23.530 align:middle line:84%
But anyway, so quick
burst of exercise.

00:54:23.530 --> 00:54:25.760 align:middle line:84%
And then number four,
make sure you're

00:54:25.760 --> 00:54:28.700 align:middle line:84%
leveraging your mental
and emotional powers.

00:54:28.700 --> 00:54:30.590 align:middle line:90%
Do not underestimate it.

00:54:30.590 --> 00:54:32.060 align:middle line:84%
Your mental and
emotional natures

00:54:32.060 --> 00:54:34.560 align:middle line:84%
are linked to the physical
body from the hormones.

00:54:34.560 --> 00:54:37.880 align:middle line:84%
So your body is the
end result of what

00:54:37.880 --> 00:54:41.420 align:middle line:84%
you're thinking and feeling and
the hormones you're producing.

00:54:41.420 --> 00:54:43.847 align:middle line:84%
Don't underestimate
the power of your mind

00:54:43.847 --> 00:54:46.430 align:middle line:84%
and the power of your feelings
and the power of your emotions.

00:54:46.430 --> 00:54:48.180 align:middle line:90%
It's unbelievably important.

00:54:48.180 --> 00:54:50.350 align:middle line:84%
And then, I say last, but
it's certainly not least.

00:54:50.350 --> 00:54:51.350 align:middle line:90%
It's the most important.

00:54:51.350 --> 00:54:52.640 align:middle line:90%
It's your spirituality.

00:54:52.640 --> 00:54:54.821 align:middle line:84%
And by that, I mean
your connection.

00:54:54.821 --> 00:54:55.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: With each other?

00:54:55.820 --> 00:54:56.990 align:middle line:90%
>>FUCHS: Every connection.

00:54:56.990 --> 00:54:58.670 align:middle line:90%
Separation is an illusion.

00:54:58.670 --> 00:55:00.440 align:middle line:10%
And it is the ultimate sin.

00:55:00.440 --> 00:55:01.870 align:middle line:10%
It is original sin.

00:55:01.870 --> 00:55:04.462 align:middle line:10%
It is this idea that we live
in a world where we're separate

00:55:04.462 --> 00:55:06.170 align:middle line:10%
and where I'm separate
from the universe.

00:55:06.170 --> 00:55:07.711 align:middle line:84%
Because that's where
fear comes from.

00:55:07.711 --> 00:55:10.730 align:middle line:84%
If I believe that I'm alone
and marooned in this universe

00:55:10.730 --> 00:55:12.439 align:middle line:84%
and everything is
around me and I'm here,

00:55:12.439 --> 00:55:13.854 align:middle line:84%
and that's what
most of us believe

00:55:13.854 --> 00:55:15.420 align:middle line:84%
and that's the way
most of us think,

00:55:15.420 --> 00:55:17.820 align:middle line:84%
obviously, I'm gonna be
in a defensive posture.

00:55:17.820 --> 00:55:18.620 align:middle line:90%
I can't help it.

00:55:18.620 --> 00:55:20.453 align:middle line:10%
I mean, I have to be
in a defensive posture.

00:55:20.453 --> 00:55:22.460 align:middle line:10%
Because the world can
come crashing down on me.

00:55:22.460 --> 00:55:25.670 align:middle line:10%
But if we believe what is really
true at the quantum level,

00:55:25.670 --> 00:55:28.100 align:middle line:10%
and even if you use
your imagination,

00:55:28.100 --> 00:55:30.560 align:middle line:10%
you can see that I'm being
created in your brain

00:55:30.560 --> 00:55:31.360 align:middle line:10%
right now.

00:55:31.360 --> 00:55:33.329 align:middle line:84%
And you're being created
in my brain right now.

00:55:33.329 --> 00:55:35.120 align:middle line:84%
And there's a oneness
that's a place that's

00:55:35.120 --> 00:55:37.650 align:middle line:84%
not only scientifically
valid, but also common sense

00:55:37.650 --> 00:55:38.450 align:middle line:90%
tells you that.

00:55:38.450 --> 00:55:41.090 align:middle line:84%
If you could truly
live in that place,

00:55:41.090 --> 00:55:44.000 align:middle line:84%
that will allow your
sympathetic nervous system

00:55:44.000 --> 00:55:46.980 align:middle line:84%
to stand down, your emergency
system, your defensive system

00:55:46.980 --> 00:55:47.780 align:middle line:90%
to stand down.

00:55:47.780 --> 00:55:49.460 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately, that's
what it's all about.

00:55:49.460 --> 00:55:50.200 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It seems like it.

00:55:50.200 --> 00:55:52.533 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: In Christianity,
they say you have to be saved.

00:55:52.533 --> 00:55:53.810 align:middle line:90%
I say you have to be safe.

00:55:53.810 --> 00:55:56.150 align:middle line:84%
You have to tell the
body it's safe so that it

00:55:56.150 --> 00:55:57.510 align:middle line:90%
can thrive and do its growth.

00:55:57.510 --> 00:55:58.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, safety is huge.

00:55:58.340 --> 00:56:00.110 align:middle line:84%
>>FUCHS: Safety, the body
has to know it's safe.

00:56:00.110 --> 00:56:02.070 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It seems there's so
much that you've taught us here.

